      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PROFESSOR STARR (3) has been going along well and was strongly fancied last time but could only manage second (19.27) at this track. Good beginner aided by a nice draw. Nicely placed to grab a well-deserved win. HOCKING (4) was game in defeat at the latest run, finishing third and beaten 1.5 lengths (25.82) behind Big Easy Al at Q Lakeside. Solid beginner who can clear the tricky draw. Must be included in calculations. CASH ON DEMAND (1) was drawn the middle but pinged the lids and led until the final stages, holding on for a place (25.77) at Q Lakeside in a Mix 5 over 457m. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings eight times from 10 starts. Bold showing expected. DAINTREE TOMMY (7) is likely to have admirers.",
